<ns1514:section xmlns:ns1514="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.enterpriseBeans.entityBeans.introduction.serverCrash">

  <ns1515:title xmlns:ns1515="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Entity beans survive server crashes</ns1515:title>
  <ns1516:para xmlns:ns1516="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Session beans do not typically survive a server crash. If a server goes down the
    sessions are typically closed and the corresponding session beans are deleted.
  </ns1516:para>
  <ns1517:para xmlns:ns1517="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Entity beans, on the other hand, are back in their original state after the server
    crash, i.e. the beans are reconstructed with the same state and same identity.
  </ns1517:para>
</ns1514:section>